main event: A Navy officer reported a sighting of green and white unidentified flying objects in Los Alamos, N.M. in February 1949.
interesting points: The report was from a credible witness, a Navy officer.
The UFOs were described as moving at a speed not as fast as an automobile and parallel to the earth.
The sighting took place in Los Alamos, N.M., a location associated with atomic research and military facilities.
The objects were not found in official files, indicating a potential discrepancy between reported sightings and documented records.
The colors of the UFOs, green and white, are not commonly associated with known aircraft or natural phenomena.
sighted object: green and white unidentified flying objects
